  "text": "Although it has been reported that PCPE-1 is not readily detectable by immunostaining in uninjured mouse cornea [CITATION_1] , immunoblotting in the present study readily detected PCPE-1 as a~55-kDa band in WT mouse cornea, while its absence in Pcolce −/− cornea demonstrated the specificity of the assay (Fig. 1a) . These results are consistent with a previous report of immunoblotting detection of PCPE-1 in cornea [CITATION_2] ). Due to the possibility of functional redundancy between PCPE-1 and PCPE-2, immunoblotting was performed to determine whether PCPE-2 is found in WT cornea. As can be seen in Fig. 1b , PCPE-2 was not detected in WT cornea, although it could be readily detected as a~48-kDa band in heart, a tissue previously demonstrated to express PCPE-2 RNA [CITATION_3] . Immunoblotting with anti-PCPE-2 antibodies was also unable to detect PCPE-2 expression in Pcolce −/− corneal extracts, indicating that corneal PCPE-2 expression is not induced in a compensatory manner in response to PCPE-1 ablation (data not shown).",
